HEADWORD: Walloons
<hw>Wal*loons"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>; <sing>sing.
<singw>Walloon</singw> <pr>(<?/)</pr></sing>. <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>wallon</ets>.]</ety> <def>A Romanic people inhabiting that part of
Belgium which comprises the provinces of Hainaut, Namur, Li⟦eacute⟧ge,
and Luxembourg, and about one third of Brabant; also, the language
spoken by this people. Used also adjectively.</def> <mark>[Written also
Wallons.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧A base <xex>Walloon</xex> . . . thrust Talbot
with a spear.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Walloon guard</b></col>, <cd>the bodyguard of the Spanish
monarch; -- so called because formerly consisting of
Walloons.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wallop</ent>⟦br⟧
